travelAdvisory.comment:
The temperature has been above freezing, even at higher elevations, causing the snow to settle and become wet. Significant melting of snow has occurred as a result across the country. Over the next few days, temperatures will cool slightly, and we can expect overnight frost, which should help strengthen the snowpack. Many avalanches released in the East and North of Iceland during the thaw and afterward, due to warming and solar radiation.





